        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Magister, if you are talking about Extended Affliction 3, which adds 20% to the DOT ticks, you can do the Coldain Military Wristguard quest.</P><P>I just did it yesterday, and it is pretty easy for any necro past lvl 50, you just have alot of running around to do (and wait for the broodmother to pop, a 12 hour spawn).  When I played last night with the wristguard, I noticed that dooming, splurt, pyro, and all dot type spells (including fear!) got the extra 20% time.  While playing, I saw that the extra time on the dot's was nice for damage, but the extra time on fear & dooming meant that on almost all dark blue mobs, I didn't have to re-cast fear or dooming darkness - this added to more pulls, faster experience!  Any necro post-50 should have this item because it's reletively easy to get and has a great focus affect.</P><P>When you do the quest, don't worry if you are ally to Coldain (the last mob you kill is a coldain dorf) - you take a hit for the coldain, but it wasn't much because I stayed ally.  I was KOS to tormax, so I had to make a warrior to do some of it - I just twinked the warrior with some +hp items to over 300 and gave her a couple hundred plat for ports/buffs (in case she died alot).  THE HARDEST PART:  getting the warrior from the iceclad port to thurg (invis wears off), and then from thurg (after bound in the city) to the wurm caves in GD.  Just have someone sow/invis you in GD, then run into the caves, take your first left, and stay in the center of the halls until you get to the broodmother.  Here's the 2 links to the quest:</P><P><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4839" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4839</a></P><P><a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=6197" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=6197</a></P><P>I had fun getting it; the best was playing a low-level character again and worrying about getting killed by spiders and orcs...LOL!</P><P>Morloch<br>58 Defiler on Tunare<br><a href="http://www.fortis-of-tunare.com">Fortis Guild</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112873">Magelo Profile</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
